{
  "_doc": "March of the Machine (MOM) Draft + Collector recipes from Wizards' 'Collecting March of the Machine' article (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-march-of-the-machine). Product lineup: Set, Draft, Collector, Jumpstart, Bundle, Commander, Prerelease \u2014 we model only Draft + Collector (authoritative). The Multiverse Legends bonus sheet is its own Scryfall set, code MUL, referenced via set:\"MUL\". Battle cards and non-battle double-faced cards are part of the MOM main set; modeled with the double_faced filter where the article calls them out as a dedicated slot. Finish filters: 'foil etched' Multiverse Legends use the etched_foil filter; 'halo foil' Multiverse Legends use the halo_foil filter (verified: all 65 MUL cards carry promo_type halofoil); 'serialized double rainbow' cards (MUL legends + the five MOM main-set Praetors) use the serialized filter (they carry promo_types serialized+doublerainbow). Approximations that remain: Commander/Jumpstart extended-art rares in Collector are approximated as MOM extended_art since those secondary sets aren't modeled; planar Booster Fun rares use showcase/borderless filters. Percentages match the article where stated. [Commander-slot fix: now references MOC (the MOM Commander set) so collector packs include Commander-deck cards.]",
